The Telegraph - Calcutta

 Amritraj approaches Federer

Chennai: Indian tennis legend Vijay Amritraj said that he has asked Roger Federer to take part in the Chennai Open. Amritraj, chairman of the organising committee said: ?We have approached Roger Federer to take part in the meet.? 

Amritraj was here on his way to Bangkok. The former Indian Davis Cup captain, meanwhile, felt a reputed foreign coach is the need of the hour to put Indian tennis back on the world map. (PTI) 

